    <weatherForecast/>
    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>Considerable avalanche danger will prevail. &lt;br/> The wind slabs represent the main danger.</highlights>
      <comment>The avalanche prone locations are to be found adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls and at transitions from a shallow to a deep snowpack. Avalanches can penetrate down to the ground. They can in many places be released, even by a single winter sport participant.  Wooded areas could also be affected by avalanches and present situations of instability. Moist avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
    <snowpackStructure>
      <comment>The weather conditions gave rise to increasing moistening of the snowpack. &lt;br/> The wind slabs of the last few days are lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack. Precarious weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on shady slopes.</comment>
    </snowpackStructure>
